wpt.desc: Hickory Hill 490ft Homerun by bizmogirl, Traditional Cache (2/1.5)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Hickory Hill 490ft Homerun
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: This cache is in Hickory Hill Park in Warwick New York. It is near a baseball field. Depending on the season you may have to cross over a small stream.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description: The cache contains a divervan coin, mini stuffed animals, a mexican coin, a key, a bell, magnets, a pin, a can opener, and a bunch of othere little things. The area is a great place for a picnic.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:encoded_hints: Two big rocks in front of the cache. The title is a hint.

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Ugh, mosquitoes. But we persevered and found the cache. Found with 19acassel.
